reviews.title: Serving lunch took 45 minutes
reviews.text: Cozy and busy. Drink order was taken quickly and brought quickly, however, the food took 45 minutes. Afterwards I said something about it, get in response: « It's crowded ». That's no excuse for me. In my opinion, you can handle too many tables for the kitchen. Then tell guests before they sit down that it takes a long time.

tips.body: Geef aan dat je haast hebt of vraag hoe lang het duurt voordat je je eten hebt.

reviews.title: Customer unfriendly and rude
reviews.text: Very unfriendly staff. After 20 minutes someone was willing to take our order. Then wait 15 minutes for a menu (they didn't have that much). After 1 hour no food and when asked if it could be faster with the food we were very rudely spoken to by staff.  Then got up and left the restaurant without a meal.  Very customer unfriendly restaurant.  The menu was also very limited

reviews.title: Lala
reviews.text:
Nice place, smooth and friendly service but chicken soup without chicken for the 3rd time in a row asparagus with sauce without taste. Too bad!
French fries and veggie tasty

reviews.title: Cozy and good
reviews.text: Delicious prawns as a starter and the house-cut tournedos as a main course. It was both super good! The service is g friendly and willing or thinking about your choices. Overall a more than fine restaurant!

reviews.title: Lady steak tough
reviews.text: It is a cozy place to eat, however today April 4, 2025 cozy with my wife ordered a lady steak. It was her birthday today. Everything else fine, but the steak, tough. Too bad, guys. This doesn't fit. You pay 30 euros for an old piece of meat. We'll be back on April 10, please be a little more tender. Reported by the way, and would be reported.

tips.body: Eerst vragen of de steak mals is

reviews.title: Dessert was disappointing. Furthermore, cozy and good food.
reviews.text:
Cozy atmosphere, delicious al la cart eaten. Friendly staff, friendly staff. Everything looks taken care of. 
My point is : 
Eton mess on dessert menu they have indicated their own interpretation. There was no sign of the crumbled merenge that belongs there. That was replaced by a few crumbs of speculaas. 
 Fresh summer fruit had been replaced by stew pears that you had to find. 
I mentioned it but the answer was . We have our own eton mess. 
I wouldn't choose this for dessert anymore.

tips.body: Bij twijfel vragen wat je mag verwachten.

reviews.title: Neat restaurant, good service, nicely decorated with a bird theme.
reviews.text:
We had a bite to eat and walked through Leek into the Dorpskamer. There were already a lot of people sitting at 5:45 PM on Saturday, we got the last table, which was nice because we had the dog with us and didn't feel like looking any further.
There are 2 parrots at the entrance, special.

It is a cafe, so not an extensive menu, but otherwise very good.

A bread board in advance, tasty bread, tasty aioli, something with sausage and tasty dip.

Wait staff were attentive and friendly. The restaurant was nicely decorated, with a bird theme.

The daily special was soles, which I chose, the 2 soles were on a bed of potatoes, also with my partner's spareribs. But it was also served with fries and a red cabbage salad.
Slip sole was delicious, we couldn't fault the red cabbage salad and the fries and potatoes were too much.

I had coffee for desert, my partner a waffle with cherries, ice cream, whipped cream. That was a very large dessert, but the waffle and cherries were a bit boring.

reviews.title: Tasty, cozy and friendly
reviews.text: Tip from the B&B owner where we stayed. Enjoyed sitting on the terrace with the dog. The food tasted excellent, well prepared, attentive, friendly service and a cozy atmosphere. Recommended, in our opinion, with something for every taste on the menu
